# NotANit — secret values
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in your credentials:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# `.env` holds the VALUES of secrets (tokens, API keys, AWS credentials). The
# YAML config references them by name — e.g. `token: ${SCM_TOKEN}` — so the
# config documents what's needed while the values stay here, out of git.
# Everything else (providers, URLs, models, region, role ARN) lives in the YAML.
#
# `.env` is gitignored and loaded automatically on startup (override the path
# with --env-file). Variables already exported in your shell take precedence.

# ── SCM token (read-only) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SCM_TOKEN works for either provider; the provider-specific ones are fallbacks.
# GitLab needs `read_api`; GitHub needs `repo` read.
SCM_TOKEN=
# GITLAB_TOKEN=
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

# ── Anthropic API key (when llm.provider = anthropic) ─────────────────────────
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ── AWS credentials (when llm.provider = bedrock) ─────────────────────────────
# Required and read only from here — Bedrock does NOT use the default AWS
# credential chain (~/.aws, instance profile, etc.).
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# Required ONLY for temporary/STS credentials (access keys starting with ASIA):
# AWS_SESSION_TOKEN=
